      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WINSOME JOSIE (7) could finish only among the minors last time (30.42) at this track, bringing a two run winning streak to an end. Form here sound including two wins. Drawn out but with clear running expected to go close. FEARLESS BANDIT (4) is better than last start when fifth (29.96) in a Grade 4/5 at this track over 520m. Solid record here winning five races. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Expected to give a good account. FLASH ETHICS (6) made it two minor placings on the trot when beaten second (29.64) in a Grade 4/5 at this track last time out. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Well placed here and should do much better. BILLY RAY'S GIRL (8) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.",
